1
00:01:32,270 --> 00:01:34,930
[How dare you!?]

2
00:01:35,030 --> 00:01:37,820
[Episode 10]

3
00:01:40,910 --> 00:01:42,710
Which company are you the CEO of?

4
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:45,350
What does this company do?

5
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:46,570
When was it listed?

6
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:48,850
What was its market cap

7
00:01:50,870 --> 00:01:52,200
before you came here?

8
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:55,430
I should just tell her everything.

9
00:01:55,430 --> 00:01:56,560
Who exactly are you?

10
00:01:58,380 --> 00:01:59,979
But if I tell the whole truth,

11
00:02:00,980 --> 00:02:03,820
that fragile bit of trust and closeness
she has with me

12
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:05,080
will probably vanish.

13
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:11,210
Between letting her doubt me
and breaking her heart,

14
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:14,140
I would rather let her keep doubting.

15
00:02:28,079 --> 00:02:29,079
I don't remember.

16
00:02:46,050 --> 00:02:47,579
If you don't want to tell me,

17
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:52,620
I won't ask again.

18
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:11,310
Your Highness!

19
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:12,000
Your Highness!

20
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,710
Wake up! Wake up!

21
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:17,570
Your Highness,

22
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:18,670
stop sleeping.

23
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:21,570
The Empress Dowager
is here to check your homework.

24
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,000
What the hell?

25
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,190
What am I wearing?

26
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,750
How did I wake up here?

27
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,870
Where am I?

28
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:57,270
I think earlier

29
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,470
I was sneaking my phone in math class

30
00:04:00,190 --> 00:04:02,710
and accidentally clicked
on a cheesy web novel

31
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:03,310
called...

32
00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:06,030
Oh right.

33
00:04:06,670 --> 00:04:10,070
It's called "Transmigrated:
The Devil's Beloved Consort"!

34
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:13,010
The Empress Dowager has arrived!

35
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:16,990
Your Majesty.

36
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,130
How is the Crown Prince's study today?

37
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:21,950
Your Majesty,

38
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:25,310
today the Crown Prince studied
the Thousand Character Classic

39
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:29,300
and learned about astronomy, geography,
and social customs.

40
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:32,240
-Devil's Favorite Concubine?
-He is a quick and eager learner

41
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,150
-Favorite Consort?
-and has already

42
00:04:33,150 --> 00:04:34,560
grasped much of the material.

43
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:37,220
So it really is a story
set in an imperial palace.

44
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:38,630
It's just that...

45
00:04:39,690 --> 00:04:40,480
Oh no.

46
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,240
How do I get back?

47
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:47,590
It hurts so much?

48
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:48,520
Here,

49
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,150
let me massage it for you.

50
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:53,200
Here.

51
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:55,580
Don't touch me, Mr. Bei.

52
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,900
Why did it flare up all of a sudden?

53
00:04:58,290 --> 00:04:59,640
It might be a brain tumor.

54
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,380
Impossible.

55
00:05:00,590 --> 00:05:01,790
I checked your pulse.

56
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:02,810
You don't have that.

57
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:04,090
I need a CT scan.

58
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:05,970
Wh-What T?

59
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:10,730
Never mind.

60
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:18,950
Mr. Bei.

61
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:21,620
I want sweet porridge.

62
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:22,070
Okay.

63
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:23,680
I'll go make some right now.

64
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,360
Just wait.

65
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:35,159
Your Majesty, Mr. Bai sent another letter,

66
00:05:35,159 --> 00:05:36,680
urging you to get rid of
the demonic consort as soon as possible.

67
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,750
She is not a demonic consort!

68
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:39,080
No need to reply to that!

69
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:39,870
Yes.

70
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:47,200
Your Highness,

71
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,340
His Majesty didn't summon you today.

72
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:51,680
Is it appropriate for us
to go there directly?

73
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,510
It's precisely because he didn't summon me

74
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:54,680
that I must go.

75
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:56,330
Why?

76
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:57,580
I don't understand.

77
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:01,950
I, Xie Yong'er, am the chosen one.

78
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:04,250
In this world, I was supposed to

79
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:05,720
have everything go my way.

80
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:08,380
But I've been in the palace for so long.

81
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:10,310
Not only have I accomplished nothing,

82
00:06:10,310 --> 00:06:12,360
but I have also been treated
like an outcast.

83
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,020
An outcast?

84
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:16,840
Now, although he says he believes me,

85
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:19,800
he hasn't summoned me
to attend him even once since then.

86
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,430
Don't you think something's off?

87
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:23,060
So, you mean...

88
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:25,710
Ling, remember,

89
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:27,780
in this harem,

90
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:30,890
one careless step can cost you your life.

91
00:06:32,870 --> 00:06:33,430
Tonight,

92
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,220
I must see His Majesty

93
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:37,100
and get to the bottom of this.

94
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:43,120
[Yongyan Hall]

95
00:06:43,930 --> 00:06:45,870
Eunuch An, I need to see His Majesty.

96
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:47,470
Please let His Majesty know.

97
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:49,780
Your Highness,

98
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:52,040
His Majesty's headache has flared up.

99
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,370
It's not convenient for him to see anyone.

100
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:55,270
Eunuch An,

101
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,400
if His Majesty is unwell,

102
00:06:57,510 --> 00:07:00,360
then all the more reason for me
to go in and attend him.

103
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:02,430
Your Highness, please go back.

104
00:07:02,870 --> 00:07:04,760
His Majesty is seeing no one tonight.

105
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:05,450
Please,

106
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:07,750
don't make things difficult for me.

107
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:21,310
[Yongyan Hall]

108
00:07:26,950 --> 00:07:29,430
Having everything go my way?

109
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:33,210
Is this how you treat the chosen one?

110
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,159
Why is she here?

111
00:07:47,710 --> 00:07:50,040
And she looks even more miserable than me.

112
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:52,870
Oh right.

113
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:54,860
She's fallen out of favor
with His Majesty.

114
00:07:54,860 --> 00:07:57,190
Then let me make things
even worse for you.

115
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:00,080
Go back first, Ling.

116
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:01,040
Okay.

117
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,410
Sister, why are you here alone?

118
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,580
Are you enjoying the rain?

119
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:24,830
Yong'er?

120
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:26,440
Why are you here?

121
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:31,490
I just went to see His Majesty,

122
00:08:32,669 --> 00:08:34,799
but I didn't even get through the door.

123
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:38,020
It seems his headache flared up

124
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:39,850
and he's not feeling well.

125
00:08:42,370 --> 00:08:43,429
His Majesty is ill?

126
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,230
You didn't know?

127
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,020
Sister.

128
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:56,410
I know you and His Majesty are in love.

129
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,100
I think this is the perfect time

130
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:01,910
for you two to patch things up.

131
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,540
Why don't you give it a try?

132
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,100
Since that's the case,

133
00:09:06,990 --> 00:09:08,050
I'll go take a look.

134
00:09:08,510 --> 00:09:10,620
Thank you for coming
to tell me about this.

135
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:11,240
Go now.

136
00:09:22,180 --> 00:09:24,180
His Majesty said he's seeing no one.

137
00:09:24,590 --> 00:09:26,320
You're just going to hit a wall.

138
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:32,280
[Yongyan Hall]

139
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,120
Dan.

140
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:49,120
Dan?

141
00:09:50,030 --> 00:09:50,940
Wanyin is here.

142
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:53,130
The porridge is ready.

143
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,530
Thanks, Mr. Bei.

144
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:56,420
Well...

145
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:58,760
You two talk.

146
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,330
You two talk.

147
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:12,390
Let me feed you.

148
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:20,530
Let's talk.

149
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,140
There's no rush.

150
00:10:24,410 --> 00:10:25,540
You should rest now.

151
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:27,210
You guessed right.

152
00:10:29,470 --> 00:10:31,110
I'm not actually a CEO.

153
00:10:37,890 --> 00:10:38,950
Before I came here,

154
00:10:39,650 --> 00:10:41,050
I was a third-rate actor.

155
00:10:42,270 --> 00:10:43,800
I played bit parts for years

156
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:45,490
and never made it big.

157
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,320
If that's all,

158
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,320
why did you lie to me?

159
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:53,400
I didn't mean to lie to you.

160
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:56,910
You first guessed that I was a CEO.

161
00:10:57,470 --> 00:11:00,600
You're not one of those
legendary alpha bosses, are you?

162
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,120
I just went along with it.

163
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,060
Why did you do that?

164
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:07,960
I...

165
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:11,480
have always had bad luck,

166
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,840
and I don't seem
to have any real talent either.

167
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,360
I thought I would die here.

168
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,240
Then,

169
00:11:22,870 --> 00:11:23,670
you showed up,

170
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:28,820
like a savior from the heavens,

171
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:31,150
holding the script

172
00:11:32,590 --> 00:11:33,850
and determined to win.

173
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:38,680
When I looked at you,

174
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:40,720
I finally felt

175
00:11:43,150 --> 00:11:45,210
that there might still be hope for me.

176
00:11:56,370 --> 00:11:57,630
You're a little...

177
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:00,360
different from how I imagined.

178
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,060
I thought

179
00:12:03,870 --> 00:12:06,200
you were carrying some deep, dark secret.

180
00:12:10,590 --> 00:12:11,640
Now you know.

181
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:14,110
I don't have much of a chance.

182
00:12:14,420 --> 00:12:16,480
Even if Prince Duan is a 2D character,

183
00:12:16,780 --> 00:12:18,780
he's 100 times more capable than me.

184
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:20,460
So that promise

185
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:21,710
still stands.

186
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:26,280
If you want to leave,

187
00:12:28,010 --> 00:12:29,470
I completely understand.

188
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:30,880
I won't stop you.

189
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:39,320
Even if you don't act pitiful,

190
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,240
I won't leave.

191
00:12:43,110 --> 00:12:44,730
You need to get better soon.

192
00:12:45,530 --> 00:12:46,700
Our future plans

193
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:48,450
still need your acting skills.

194
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:57,510
Why are your clothes all wet?

195
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:58,860
I just got caught in a bit of rain.

196
00:12:58,860 --> 00:13:00,200
I'll go back and change.

197
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:01,200
Why don't you

198
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:02,360
take a hot bath here?

199
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:08,480
If you catch a cold,

200
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:11,420
who's going to take care of me,
the patient?

201
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:56,520
[Xiao Tiancai]

202
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:01,260
Which palace are you from?

203
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:03,240
Don't stand in this heavy rain.

204
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:05,570
Go into the flower house and take shelter.

205
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:07,770
What are you waiting for? Go on in.

206
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:11,770
Hurry up.

207
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,620
Wait until the rain lets up
before you head back.

208
00:14:25,330 --> 00:14:26,460
Take this umbrella.

209
00:14:29,020 --> 00:14:30,950
Don't get caught in the rain again.

210
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,340
If you catch a cold,

211
00:14:33,390 --> 00:14:34,850
at best you'll get a fever,

212
00:14:35,290 --> 00:14:37,450
and at worst it could affect
your internal organs.

213
00:14:37,450 --> 00:14:38,980
That would be real trouble.

214
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:42,470
This is mugwort.

215
00:14:42,830 --> 00:14:44,200
Take it back and smoke this spot,

216
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,200
the Fengchi point.

217
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,480
It helps dispel cold and dampness.

218
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,880
It's best not to get sick.

219
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:02,970
What is this?

220
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:06,360
This is called danggui.

221
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,100
It grows along the northwestern border.

222
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:09,770
Some time ago,

223
00:15:09,770 --> 00:15:10,470
the Imperial Hospital wanted

224
00:15:10,470 --> 00:15:12,670
to compile a catalog of medicinal herbs

225
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:15,340
and study their effects
and growing conditions,

226
00:15:15,340 --> 00:15:18,670
so they had people bring back
a few plants from the northwest

227
00:15:18,830 --> 00:15:20,090
and planted them here.

228
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,560
They were fresh and lovely at first

229
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:24,090
and grew a lot in just 3 days.

230
00:15:25,110 --> 00:15:26,320
But for some reason,

231
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:29,480
after they bloomed, they began to wither.

232
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:33,440
The same species can be very different

233
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:35,040
in different environments.

234
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:37,050
The northwest is cold.

235
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,730
If you plant it here,

236
00:15:40,030 --> 00:15:41,430
it surely won't survive.

237
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,540
That's not entirely true.

238
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,000
Plants are like people.

239
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,460
They have strong vitality

240
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:51,790
and will try hard
to adapt to different environments.

241
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:53,240
Dandelions take root wherever they land.

242
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,630
Wild grass grows back stronger
after burning.

243
00:15:54,630 --> 00:15:57,260
Sometimes the price of survival

244
00:15:57,550 --> 00:15:59,030
is not being as lush as before,

245
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:00,430
or bearing fewer fruits,

246
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:02,290
but that's the law of survival.

247
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:03,330
Look at that.

248
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,040
Lilyturf.

249
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:06,320
It's also known as the "immortal herb."

250
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:07,720
Whether it's dry or damp,

251
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:08,780
warm or cold,

252
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:10,290
it survives just fine.

253
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:12,860
That's easy for you to say.

254
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:15,060
With a flick of your fingers,

255
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:17,130
you decide whether it lives or dies.

256
00:16:17,510 --> 00:16:19,910
But has anyone ever asked
if it was willing?

257
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:22,330
Maybe death is its way of protesting.

258
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,640
It... it's just a plant.

259
00:16:28,230 --> 00:16:29,360
Miss, can you tell me

260
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:32,150
how you know whether it's willing or not?

261
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:33,460
I just feel

262
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:36,760
it shouldn't have been taken away
from home

263
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:39,660
to grow
in this completely unfamiliar place

264
00:16:39,910 --> 00:16:40,970
and wither here.

265
00:16:41,630 --> 00:16:42,760
What did it do wrong?

266
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:45,180
Why should it go through all this?

267
00:16:47,810 --> 00:16:49,100
You have a soft heart.

268
00:16:50,670 --> 00:16:51,870
It pains me deeply

269
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,820
that they didn't survive.

270
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:56,520
I come every day
to mist them and cool them down.

271
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:58,030
I even prepare ice every day

272
00:16:58,030 --> 00:17:00,510
to recreate a cold,
damp environment for them.

273
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:02,110
Though they suffer greatly,

274
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,330
they aren't alone,

275
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:06,030
nor are they facing all this
by themselves.

276
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:06,790
If,

277
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:08,960
as you say,

278
00:17:09,349 --> 00:17:10,130
they truly

279
00:17:10,550 --> 00:17:12,079
have thoughts of their own,

280
00:17:12,650 --> 00:17:14,510
then seeing someone watch over them

281
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:15,880
and make an effort for them

282
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:18,339
might give them a bit more will
to keep going.

283
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:26,690
Even a herb has someone watching over it,

284
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,920
going through hardships together.

285
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:31,750
Yet I have always been alone.

286
00:17:42,170 --> 00:17:43,500
Are you feeling better?

287
00:17:43,790 --> 00:17:44,720
I ate something,

288
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:45,940
and I'm better now.

289
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:47,590
Well,

290
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,510
if there's nothing else,

291
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:52,160
I'll go back now.

292
00:17:53,730 --> 00:17:55,930
♪ A letter, a line of words ♪

293
00:17:56,140 --> 00:17:57,720
♪ Picking up the pen again and again ♪

294
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,270
What's wrong?

295
00:17:57,730 --> 00:17:59,890
♪ A cup of tea, a glass of wine ♪

296
00:17:58,780 --> 00:18:00,250
Is your head hurting again?

297
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:01,670
♪ Drinking alone, hard to get drunk ♪

298
00:18:00,830 --> 00:18:01,720
It's starting to hurt again.

299
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:04,040
♪ Words unspoken ♪

300
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:05,640
Why don't you stay?

301
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:08,080
♪ Shyness unhidden ♪

302
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,140
Your hair is still wet,

303
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:11,940
♪ Walking down a street together ♪

304
00:18:09,940 --> 00:18:11,400
and it's raining outside.

305
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:13,570
♪ Shoulder to shoulder ♪

306
00:18:13,780 --> 00:18:15,740
♪ Raising my head, lowering my eyes ♪

307
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:14,360
But...

308
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,680
But I'm supposed to be playing
the out-of-favor role right now.

309
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:17,610
♪ Blushing slightly ♪

310
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:20,130
♪ A face flushed red at first sight ♪

311
00:18:18,270 --> 00:18:20,160
It wouldn't be appropriate for me to stay.

312
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:21,490
Then let's just treat it

313
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:25,160
♪ A smile like a flower in my heart ♪

314
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:23,000
as a day off.

315
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:26,500
Forget about the tyrant
and the demonic consort.

316
00:18:25,660 --> 00:18:29,050
♪ Whose longing lingers day and night? ♪

317
00:18:26,830 --> 00:18:29,630
Forget about Prince Duan
and the Empress Dowager.

318
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:32,780
♪ Piling up stories
and countless thoughts ♪

319
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,130
Just for one day.

320
00:18:33,140 --> 00:18:35,090
♪ Walking through once, taking a glance ♪

321
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:33,720
Okay?

322
00:18:35,270 --> 00:18:37,000
♪ All lingering and wandering ♪

323
00:18:37,210 --> 00:18:39,070
♪ How many rains, how many winds? ♪

324
00:18:39,220 --> 00:18:41,320
♪ Looking back, it's all like smoke ♪

325
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,950
♪ Watching the hazy world ♪

326
00:18:45,770 --> 00:18:48,100
♪ Who still guards that yearning? ♪

327
00:18:48,170 --> 00:18:49,310
♪ Still unchanged ♪

328
00:18:49,780 --> 00:18:52,590
♪ Even if months and years
pass in a blink ♪

329
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,800
♪ One thought for a lifetime ♪

330
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:59,180
♪ Waiting for someone to appear ♪

331
00:19:02,150 --> 00:19:03,980
Then let's stop thinking about anything

332
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:05,180
and have a good sleep.

333
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:17,140
♪ Whose longing lingers day and night? ♪

334
00:19:17,690 --> 00:19:20,630
♪ Piling up stories
and countless thoughts ♪

335
00:19:21,220 --> 00:19:23,290
♪ Walking through once, taking a glance ♪

336
00:19:23,290 --> 00:19:25,020
♪ All lingering and wandering ♪

337
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:27,130
♪ How many rains, how many winds? ♪

338
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:29,340
♪ Looking back, it's all like smoke ♪

339
00:19:29,770 --> 00:19:32,980
♪ Watching the hazy world ♪

340
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:36,160
♪ Who still guards that yearning? ♪

341
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:36,280
Goodnight.

342
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,340
♪ Still unchanged ♪

343
00:19:37,790 --> 00:19:40,700
♪ Even if months and years
pass in a blink ♪

344
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:42,760
♪ One thought for a lifetime ♪

345
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:50,110
♪ Waiting for someone to appear ♪

346
00:20:02,650 --> 00:20:05,450
That fire in the library last time
was terrifying.

347
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:07,840
Although it's being renovated now,

348
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,750
safety isn't guaranteed.

349
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:11,500
If you ask me,

350
00:20:11,870 --> 00:20:14,000
My Lady, you shouldn't have come here.

351
00:20:14,020 --> 00:20:15,100
It's fine.

352
00:20:15,370 --> 00:20:16,920
Isn't Madam Bei at the door?

353
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:18,410
It's absolutely safe.

354
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,790
The history of Yan State is so convoluted.

355
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:22,520
And it has nothing to do with us.

356
00:20:23,350 --> 00:20:25,750
My Lady,
be careful not to strain your eyes.

357
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:27,370
It's fine.

358
00:20:27,390 --> 00:20:28,850
My eyesight is excellent.

359
00:20:30,110 --> 00:20:33,160
My Lady, are you even listening to me?

360
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:34,690
Take a break.

361
00:20:35,030 --> 00:20:36,160
Look at the scenery.

362
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:37,680
My Lady, look.

363
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:41,410
The hydrangeas in the field
are blooming beautifully.

364
00:20:51,780 --> 00:20:52,380
What's...

365
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:53,760
going on?

366
00:20:54,270 --> 00:20:55,720
-Beautiful, right?
-SOS?

367
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:58,580
It's just that the arrangement
looks a bit strange.

368
00:20:58,710 --> 00:20:59,190
Mei.

369
00:20:59,980 --> 00:21:00,670
Do you know

370
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,490
who planted these flowers?

371
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,080
I don't know.

372
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,360
Put the book back.

373
00:21:05,370 --> 00:21:06,430
I'll go take a look.

374
00:21:09,030 --> 00:21:09,650
Wanyin!

375
00:21:09,820 --> 00:21:10,270
Wan...

376
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:12,840
Mei!

377
00:21:13,030 --> 00:21:14,030
Get the umbrella!

378
00:21:14,050 --> 00:21:14,570
Go!

379
00:21:22,850 --> 00:21:29,640
[SOS]

380
00:21:24,810 --> 00:21:25,330
This...

381
00:21:26,820 --> 00:21:29,150
Could this be planted by a transmigrator?

382
00:21:29,450 --> 00:21:30,110
In Devil's Favorite Concubine,

383
00:21:30,110 --> 00:21:31,970
there is absolutely no such plot.

384
00:21:32,270 --> 00:21:33,560
Could it be that before we came,

385
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:35,020
there were others like us?

386
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:38,410
If it really was left by a transmigrator,

387
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,920
there must be other clues nearby.

388
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:46,710
[SOS]

389
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:47,780
Noble Consort？

390
00:21:49,060 --> 00:21:51,140
The rain is so heavy today.

391
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,940
Why aren't you using an umbrella?

392
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:58,120
Crown Prince?

393
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:00,240
Why are you out here alone?

394
00:22:01,770 --> 00:22:02,690
Your Highness.

395
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:06,110
I'm here to enjoy the flowers.

396
00:22:07,650 --> 00:22:08,820
Could he also be...

397
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,260
Crown Prince.

398
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:12,740
In front of my house are two trees.

399
00:22:12,830 --> 00:22:13,830
One is a date tree.

400
00:22:14,030 --> 00:22:15,280
What is the other one?

401
00:22:18,890 --> 00:22:20,270
"Before my bed, the moonlight glows."

402
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:21,670
Do you know the next line?

403
00:22:24,290 --> 00:22:26,030
-"It looks like frost..."
-Your Highness!

404
00:22:26,030 --> 00:22:27,030
Your Highness!

405
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:29,790
Greetings, Your Highness.

406
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:31,960
Your Highness,
I've been looking everywhere for you.

407
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,440
The Empress Dowager is waiting for you.

408
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,270
Your Highness,

409
00:22:34,270 --> 00:22:36,870
I will take His Highness back
to his palace now.

410
00:22:49,690 --> 00:22:50,170
CEO Dan!

411
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:51,450
CEO Dan!

412
00:22:52,810 --> 00:22:54,560
Guess what I found in the library.

413
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:54,940
What?

414
00:22:57,070 --> 00:22:58,180
SOS.

415
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:03,140
SOS?

416
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:04,200
Yeah.

417
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:06,010
That distress signal.

418
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:08,680
I had always been on the 2nd floor before.

419
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:10,910
Today, I went up to the 3rd floor
to look for books about Yan State.

420
00:23:10,910 --> 00:23:13,470
Through an inconspicuous window,
I happened

421
00:23:13,560 --> 00:23:16,020
to catch sight of an open space
beneath the library.

422
00:23:16,020 --> 00:23:18,030
Someone had planted flowers

423
00:23:18,060 --> 00:23:19,390
spelling out a huge SOS.

424
00:23:20,030 --> 00:23:21,740
So there must be
another transmigrator here

425
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:22,560
like us.

426
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:27,120
Could it have been Xie Yong'er?

427
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:31,180
That's what I thought at first.

428
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:36,110
But everything she says and does
is written in the book.

429
00:23:36,110 --> 00:23:38,370
There's not a word about asking for help.

430
00:23:38,990 --> 00:23:40,320
It must be someone else.

431
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:43,950
We've been here for so long.

432
00:23:44,180 --> 00:23:46,040
If there had been anyone strange,

433
00:23:46,130 --> 00:23:47,770
we would have noticed long ago.

434
00:23:47,770 --> 00:23:48,940
What if that person

435
00:23:48,970 --> 00:23:50,760
has been trying hard to hide themselves?

436
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:52,360
They don't know who to trust,

437
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:53,650
so they have to use this

438
00:23:53,650 --> 00:23:55,180
subtle way to call for help.

439
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:56,940
Exactly.

440
00:23:57,570 --> 00:24:00,000
I need to find out
who planted this flower field.

441
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:00,670
Wait.

442
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:03,620
Don't rush.

443
00:24:04,650 --> 00:24:06,250
You think it's an SOS signal.

444
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:07,370
Maybe

445
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:10,030
the person who planted it
intended it to be

446
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:11,600
"Two Dragons Playing with a Pearl."

447
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,390
I know.

448
00:24:13,420 --> 00:24:14,180
But what if

449
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,970
there really is someone calling for help?

450
00:24:17,630 --> 00:24:19,110
Just like I was back then.

451
00:24:20,490 --> 00:24:21,710
If I hadn't met you,

452
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,620
I would be so scared struggling alone

453
00:24:24,620 --> 00:24:25,750
in this other world.

454
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:28,720
Use your imagination.

455
00:24:29,420 --> 00:24:31,080
If we really find that person,

456
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:32,940
we can play poker.

457
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:34,840
Do you think

458
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:36,910
this person is a man or a woman?

459
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:38,430
Would they like hot pot?

460
00:24:39,020 --> 00:24:40,950
Would they become friends with us?

461
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:10,040
What's wrong?

462
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,240
I asked around.

463
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:15,310
They all said

464
00:25:16,270 --> 00:25:17,200
in recent years,

465
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,500
no one has touched that flower field.

466
00:25:21,470 --> 00:25:21,990
See?

467
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,000
I told you.

468
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,420
You were overthinking it.

469
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:27,030
From a distance,

470
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,270
it really looked like

471
00:25:28,270 --> 00:25:30,150
a miraculous SOS signal.

472
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:32,430
Then here comes the problem.

473
00:25:32,550 --> 00:25:34,950
These flowers have just started blooming,

474
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,660
and will bloom for a long time.

475
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,830
What if Xie Yong'er passes by one day,

476
00:25:38,830 --> 00:25:39,830
and just like you,

477
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,480
sees the
"Two Dragons Playing with a Pearl"

478
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,590
as an SOS signal?

479
00:25:43,310 --> 00:25:43,790
Guess

480
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:46,310
what she would think.

481
00:25:48,810 --> 00:25:51,610
She'd also suspect
there's one of her kind nearby.

482
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:53,550
She might have a sudden epiphany

483
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,330
and suspect us.

484
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:57,460
Then...

485
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:59,540
Then we can't keep this field.

486
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:02,020
Can we find an excuse to remove it?

487
00:26:03,110 --> 00:26:03,680
Please.

488
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,910
Do I need an excuse

489
00:26:08,270 --> 00:26:09,670
for renovating a garden?

490
00:26:19,830 --> 00:26:20,160
What?

491
00:26:21,310 --> 00:26:23,170
Just call it my wild imagination.

492
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,770
I'm still thinking,

493
00:26:25,110 --> 00:26:26,830
what if there really was someone
like us who went through

494
00:26:26,830 --> 00:26:29,920
so much trouble planting all those flowers
to ask for help,

495
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,520
only to get no response at all

496
00:26:32,110 --> 00:26:34,170
and even have the flowers pulled out.

497
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:37,550
Should we bury something there instead?

498
00:26:37,550 --> 00:26:38,070
Like...

499
00:26:38,310 --> 00:26:39,440
a note or something?

500
00:26:41,830 --> 00:26:44,090
There's a risk Xie Yong'er might find it.

501
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:45,800
True.

502
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:51,240
Anyway, the person who planted them

503
00:26:51,590 --> 00:26:53,120
doesn't need them anymore.

504
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:54,930
What?

505
00:26:57,470 --> 00:26:58,200
I said,

506
00:26:59,750 --> 00:27:01,150
you look so pretty today.

507
00:27:06,100 --> 00:27:06,860
[Promoting Yan millet]

508
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,150
[Commoners: Food]
[Ministry of Revenue: Money]

509
00:27:08,150 --> 00:27:09,420
[Empress Dowager: Power
[Prince Duan: Opposition]

510
00:27:12,830 --> 00:27:15,090
Still thinking about Li Yunxi's method?

511
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:19,770
I thought he explained it pretty clearly.

512
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:22,590
There's nothing wrong
with the method itself.

513
00:27:22,590 --> 00:27:24,010
What worries me

514
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:26,240
is whether it can actually be carried out.

515
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:27,170
What do you mean?

516
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:28,680
Look,

517
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:30,950
back when I was an editor,

518
00:27:31,590 --> 00:27:33,450
for a project to launch smoothly,

519
00:27:33,510 --> 00:27:35,770
it had to satisfy several groups' needs.

520
00:27:36,110 --> 00:27:37,440
The producers want to save money,

521
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:38,510
the screenwriters want credit,

522
00:27:38,510 --> 00:27:39,920
the directors want artistic freedom,

523
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:41,720
and the platforms want ratings.

524
00:27:41,830 --> 00:27:44,230
Different positions, different demands.

525
00:27:44,590 --> 00:27:46,000
Only when everyone's needs are met

526
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,800
could the project move forward.

527
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,150
Go on.

528
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:52,510
So, by the same logic,

529
00:27:53,030 --> 00:27:55,160
to promote the planting of Yan millet,

530
00:27:55,570 --> 00:27:57,900
we have to satisfy several groups at once.

531
00:27:58,330 --> 00:27:59,680
You mean...

532
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:03,560
The Empress Dowager wants power,

533
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:05,290
[Empress Dowager: Power]
[Dignity]

534
00:28:05,450 --> 00:28:07,280
so the decree can't come from me.

535
00:28:08,260 --> 00:28:09,860
[Ministry of Revenue: Money]
[Chen Danian]

536
00:28:08,460 --> 00:28:10,120
The Ministry of Revenue has no money,

537
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,940
so the funds must come from elsewhere.

538
00:28:11,210 --> 00:28:12,280
[Commoners: Food][Why plant?]

539
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,290
Prince Duan opposes me,

540
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:17,520
so I can't be the one benefiting.

541
00:28:17,890 --> 00:28:19,210
Not bad, CEO Dan.

542
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:20,700
You catch on fast.

543
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:29,160
This is a place where the finest energies
of heaven and earth converge,

544
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:31,270
where yin and yang merge.

545
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:35,200
The dragon veins, surrounding hills,
and water are all perfectly aligned.

546
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:35,930
The terrain,

547
00:28:36,070 --> 00:28:36,880
momentum,

548
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:38,390
feng shui, and qi

549
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:40,140
all are auspicious.

550
00:28:40,550 --> 00:28:41,280
This is...

551
00:28:41,350 --> 00:28:42,380
In other words,

552
00:28:43,030 --> 00:28:44,270
this is the best place

553
00:28:45,550 --> 00:28:46,750
to build a mausoleum?

554
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:48,270
Exactly.

555
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,740
The Empress Dowager has been

556
00:28:56,830 --> 00:28:58,480
working tirelessly for the state.

557
00:28:58,480 --> 00:29:01,270
Your Majesty,
your wish to build a mausoleum for her

558
00:29:01,270 --> 00:29:04,590
is truly moving.

559
00:29:07,510 --> 00:29:08,590
For many years,

560
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:13,510
we've been unable to find a suitable site.

561
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:17,920
Now that the Empress Dowager's birthday
is approaching,

562
00:29:19,070 --> 00:29:20,530
the Imperial Observatory

563
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:24,330
has identified Mount Bei
as an auspicious location.

564
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:26,140
I am deeply gratified.

565
00:29:28,870 --> 00:29:30,070
Ministry of Revenue.

566
00:29:30,790 --> 00:29:32,050
Is there enough money?

567
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:34,400
Well...

568
00:29:35,310 --> 00:29:37,310
Your Majesty,
could you please tell me why?

569
00:29:37,310 --> 00:29:38,840
Did I do something wrong?

570
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:56,000
Are my eyes playing tricks on me,

571
00:29:56,510 --> 00:29:57,800
or am I seeing a ghost?

572
00:29:58,440 --> 00:29:59,700
Aren't you already...

573
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:01,300
Your Majesty.

574
00:30:01,940 --> 00:30:02,870
The f-former...

575
00:30:03,150 --> 00:30:06,220
The former Minister of Revenue was my...

576
00:30:07,260 --> 00:30:08,060
twin brother.

577
00:30:13,780 --> 00:30:16,240
It seems the position
of Minister of Revenue

578
00:30:17,350 --> 00:30:19,090
is run by your family.

579
00:30:19,550 --> 00:30:20,550
No, Your Majesty.

580
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:21,860
It's not like that.

581
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:22,680
It's just that...

582
00:30:22,680 --> 00:30:24,680
everyone in our Chen family
is willing to serve Great Xia

583
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:27,370
to our last breath, Your Majesty.

584
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:29,690
Don't panic.

585
00:30:31,030 --> 00:30:33,090
I won't punish people collectively.

586
00:30:33,720 --> 00:30:36,740
As long as you raise the funds to build
the Empress Dowager's

587
00:30:36,740 --> 00:30:37,730
mausoleum,

588
00:30:42,250 --> 00:30:43,510
I will even reward you.

589
00:30:50,550 --> 00:30:51,980
Forgive me, Your Majesty.

590
00:30:51,980 --> 00:30:53,040
Allow me to report!

591
00:30:53,590 --> 00:30:54,080
Speak.

592
00:30:55,090 --> 00:30:56,660
The mausoleum project is massive,

593
00:30:56,660 --> 00:30:58,620
but the treasury is tight at the moment.

594
00:30:58,620 --> 00:30:59,330
Unless...

595
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:01,150
Unless what?

596
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:02,610
We raise taxes!

597
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:03,960
Raise taxes?

598
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:04,590
Raise taxes?

599
00:31:04,590 --> 00:31:05,420
How can we do that?

600
00:31:05,420 --> 00:31:06,090
Indeed.

601
00:31:08,570 --> 00:31:12,170
The Ministry of Revenue
proposes raising taxes again this year.

602
00:31:12,350 --> 00:31:13,550
What do you all think?

603
00:31:15,590 --> 00:31:16,050
Well...

604
00:31:25,790 --> 00:31:27,470
Since none of you has reached a decision,

605
00:31:27,470 --> 00:31:28,390
stay here

606
00:31:29,550 --> 00:31:33,210
and discuss it until you reach
a conclusion before the court ends.

607
00:31:35,130 --> 00:31:37,370
Your Majesty.

608
00:31:38,060 --> 00:31:39,150
I heard

609
00:31:39,170 --> 00:31:40,420
that His Majesty
plans to build a mausoleum

610
00:31:40,420 --> 00:31:43,360
at Mount Bei for you as a birthday gift.

611
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:47,960
I'm both happy and helpless.

612
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,650
How so?

613
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:52,890
I'm happy

614
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:55,550
because His Majesty and Your Majesty
share such a deep mother-son bond.

615
00:31:55,550 --> 00:31:57,080
It makes everyone envious.

616
00:31:58,480 --> 00:31:59,960
And the helpless part?

617
00:32:01,110 --> 00:32:02,770
I am helpless because...

618
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,790
the gift from His Majesty is so grand

619
00:32:04,790 --> 00:32:07,000
that anything we give

620
00:32:07,020 --> 00:32:08,620
will seem insignificant.

621
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:11,980
Flatterer.

622
00:32:18,590 --> 00:32:22,280
Building a mausoleum
wastes money and manpower.

623
00:32:23,270 --> 00:32:26,830
Those who know
see it's the emperor's filial devotion

624
00:32:26,830 --> 00:32:28,160
acting on his own.

625
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:29,770
Those who don't

626
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:31,220
might think I

627
00:32:31,550 --> 00:32:33,150
do not care about the people.

628
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:36,070
The Ministry of Revenue is short on money.

629
00:32:36,070 --> 00:32:37,250
Let's put

630
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:38,970
this matter aside for now.

631
00:32:38,970 --> 00:32:41,170
Your words are mistaken, Your Majesty.

632
00:32:42,850 --> 00:32:44,020
In every dynasty,

633
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:46,800
the Empress Dowager's mausoleum
isn't just a tomb—

634
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,620
it represents the royal prestige

635
00:32:48,620 --> 00:32:51,220
and is the highest honor
for women of the harem.

636
00:32:51,430 --> 00:32:52,480
Our Great Xia thrives

637
00:32:52,480 --> 00:32:54,780
and the people prosper

638
00:32:55,290 --> 00:32:57,890
thanks to Your Majesty's
careful management.

639
00:32:58,130 --> 00:32:58,790
Do you

640
00:33:00,150 --> 00:33:03,080
want to be outshone
by the previous Empress Dowager?

641
00:33:04,550 --> 00:33:06,250
You certainly are bold.

642
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:07,830
I only said

643
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:09,880
what others want to say but dare not.

644
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:12,350
The construction of the mausoleum

645
00:33:12,350 --> 00:33:13,880
is known by the whole court.

646
00:33:13,980 --> 00:33:14,950
Stopping it now

647
00:33:15,510 --> 00:33:17,110
would be truly disgraceful.

648
00:33:18,350 --> 00:33:19,150
Your Majesty,

649
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:21,390
we absolutely can't do this.

650
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:26,910
Really?

651
00:33:27,110 --> 00:33:27,750
Yes.

652
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:31,160
Yes, indeed.

653
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:32,910
Right.

654
00:33:35,510 --> 00:33:37,040
Then tell me,

655
00:33:37,830 --> 00:33:40,830
how should this mausoleum be built?

656
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,270
I...

657
00:33:47,830 --> 00:33:48,580
Make way!

658
00:33:48,830 --> 00:33:50,690
Irrelevant persons, stand back!

659
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:04,450
Your Majesty!

660
00:34:04,450 --> 00:34:05,000
What are you doing?

661
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:05,800
Your Majesty!

662
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:08,090
Your Majesty! I demand to see you!

663
00:34:08,710 --> 00:34:09,480
Your Majesty!

664
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:10,210
How dare you!

665
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:12,590
Startling His Majesty
is a capital offense!

666
00:34:12,590 --> 00:34:13,670
I'm dying anyway!

667
00:34:14,190 --> 00:34:15,050
Your Majesty!

668
00:34:15,190 --> 00:34:16,739
Please show mercy!

669
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:17,960
Otherwise, I will die

670
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,280
with my grievances unresolved!

671
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,590
-Drag him away now!
-Your Majesty!

672
00:34:20,590 --> 00:34:21,510
-Your Majesty!
-Hurry!

673
00:34:21,510 --> 00:34:22,190
Your Majesty!

674
00:34:22,190 --> 00:34:22,800
Your Majesty!

675
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:23,429
Stop!

676
00:34:24,280 --> 00:34:24,719
Wait.

677
00:34:27,630 --> 00:34:28,280
Let him go.

678
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:29,560
Let him go!

679
00:34:30,510 --> 00:34:32,480
I am here. If you have any grievance,

680
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,139
tell me everything in detail.

681
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:37,679
Your Majesty,

682
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:39,900
please show mercy

683
00:34:42,030 --> 00:34:43,909
and leave us a way to live.

684
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:48,820
How is there no way to live?

685
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,239
Your Majesty,

686
00:34:55,190 --> 00:34:57,250
you live in luxury within the palace.

687
00:34:58,400 --> 00:35:01,230
Do you know what kind of life
the common people are living?

688
00:35:01,230 --> 00:35:02,800
A single vegetable like this

689
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,130
sells only for one coin,

690
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:06,360
but taxes take up more than half of it.

691
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:07,750
After deducting costs,

692
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:08,920
the actual profit

693
00:35:09,670 --> 00:35:11,030
is less than a tenth.

694
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:12,970
All my fellow villagers

695
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:15,280
toil from

696
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:17,440
dawn to dusk.

697
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:19,560
Yet after all that labor,

698
00:35:20,150 --> 00:35:22,010
the grain left at year's end

699
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:24,370
is only enough to stave off hunger.

700
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:25,150
My...

701
00:35:25,590 --> 00:35:27,250
My younger brother and sister

702
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:29,590
were born into a year of poor harvest

703
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:31,480
and starved to death.

704
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:33,650
They didn't even get the chance

705
00:35:35,150 --> 00:35:36,280
to see this world.

706
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:43,650
These lines...

707
00:35:47,070 --> 00:35:48,730
My younger brother and sister

708
00:35:49,150 --> 00:35:50,470
were born into

709
00:35:50,710 --> 00:35:53,800
a year of poor harvest
and starved to death.

710
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:56,280
Your Majesty,

711
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:59,360
my family
is already struggling to survive.

712
00:35:59,860 --> 00:36:01,850
Now that taxes are rising again,

713
00:36:02,070 --> 00:36:03,750
I fear even my elderly parents

714
00:36:06,590 --> 00:36:07,990
won't be able to survive.

715
00:36:17,450 --> 00:36:19,070
This is driving the common people

716
00:36:19,070 --> 00:36:20,000
to a dead end!

717
00:36:20,550 --> 00:36:21,510
What are you doing?

718
00:36:21,510 --> 00:36:22,760
The mood is just right.

719
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:23,890
Why did you stand up?

720
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,820
They are driving us to our deaths!

721
00:36:27,150 --> 00:36:28,540
Yes, Your Majesty!

722
00:36:28,590 --> 00:36:30,190
No more tax increases!

723
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:34,760
Your Majesty, no more tax increases!

724
00:36:35,630 --> 00:36:37,420
How can this be?

725
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:41,960
Bring the Minister of Revenue to me
at once!

726
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,500
Yes, Your Majesty!

727
00:36:48,070 --> 00:36:51,470
Your Majesty, Chen Danian,
the Minister of Revenue, is here.

728
00:36:51,590 --> 00:36:52,390
Your Majesty!

729
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:54,000
I am innocent!

730
00:36:54,150 --> 00:36:57,010
Why is the Ministry of Revenue
raising taxes again?

731
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:58,300
Well...

732
00:36:59,670 --> 00:37:01,230
Didn't Your Majesty want to build

733
00:37:01,230 --> 00:37:03,230
the Empress Dowager's...

734
00:37:11,150 --> 00:37:11,720
Yes.

735
00:37:12,590 --> 00:37:13,800
It was me.

736
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:15,690
I thought that

737
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:19,100
building the Empress Dowager's mausoleum
must not be done carelessly,

738
00:37:19,100 --> 00:37:19,740
but...

739
00:37:19,890 --> 00:37:21,690
but there weren't enough funds.

740
00:37:21,820 --> 00:37:22,560
So...

741
00:37:22,590 --> 00:37:23,470
No money?

742
00:37:24,810 --> 00:37:27,190
And with no money, you think you can
take our lives as payment?

743
00:37:27,190 --> 00:37:28,050
Let go!

744
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,470
In that case,

745
00:37:29,590 --> 00:37:30,920
our family has no choice

746
00:37:31,510 --> 00:37:32,960
but to cut off our heads

747
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:34,570
and offer a bowl of hot blood

748
00:37:34,910 --> 00:37:36,680
to Your Majesty!

749
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,650
"The ruler relies on the state,

750
00:37:50,230 --> 00:37:52,000
and the state relies on the people."

751
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:53,400
Such a simple truth,

752
00:37:54,380 --> 00:37:56,440
and yet you, the Minister of Revenue,

753
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:58,000
don't understand it?

754
00:37:59,300 --> 00:38:00,520
I want to ask you,

755
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:02,810
why are the funds for the mausoleum

756
00:38:03,220 --> 00:38:05,230
not taken from the state treasury?

757
00:38:06,310 --> 00:38:06,830
Well...

758
00:38:10,710 --> 00:38:11,580
I was wrong.

759
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,820
I was wrong!

760
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:16,260
Take me to the state treasury!

761
00:38:16,270 --> 00:38:18,250
Your Majesty, you cannot go there!

762
00:38:18,270 --> 00:38:19,430
Today, I must...

763
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:24,330
I must give an explanation
to the people of Great Xia!

764
00:38:26,110 --> 00:38:27,740
Your Majesty is wise!

765
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:32,190
Your Majesty is wise!
Your Majesty is wise!

766
00:38:32,220 --> 00:38:37,590
Your Majesty is wise!
Your Majesty is wise!

767
00:38:56,590 --> 00:38:57,320
What is it?

768
00:38:58,190 --> 00:38:58,990
Why the panic?

769
00:38:59,510 --> 00:39:00,930
The Emperor publicly berated
the Minister of Revenue

770
00:39:00,930 --> 00:39:02,360
over the tax increase.

771
00:39:02,890 --> 00:39:03,960
Now he's escorting him

772
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:05,560
to the Ministry's treasury.

773
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:10,280
He has an ulterior motive.

774
00:39:15,150 --> 00:39:16,030
I knew

775
00:39:17,070 --> 00:39:19,530
building the mausoleum wasn't that simple.

776
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:21,110
It seems our Emperor

777
00:39:22,190 --> 00:39:24,190
is going after the Empress Dowager.

778
00:39:27,550 --> 00:39:30,210
Since they're putting each other
over the fire,

779
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:33,730
I might as well

780
00:39:38,210 --> 00:39:39,600
add fuel to the flames.

781
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:47,250
Zhang San's Diary.

782
00:39:47,670 --> 00:39:51,120
Are there other transmigrators like me?

783
00:39:53,670 --> 00:39:54,620
Wait.

784
00:40:01,850 --> 00:40:02,510
"Yuanfang,

785
00:40:03,140 --> 00:40:04,200
what do you think?"

786
00:40:04,260 --> 00:40:06,110
My name is not Yuanfang.

787
00:40:06,250 --> 00:40:07,700
"I simply cannot do it!"

788
00:40:07,910 --> 00:40:08,530
I...

789
00:40:08,550 --> 00:40:09,880
I am just a servant!

790
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:13,040
"Imperial Jade Wine.

791
00:40:13,230 --> 00:40:14,430
180 for a cup."

792
00:40:14,610 --> 00:40:16,010
Spare me, Your Highness!

793
00:40:18,970 --> 00:40:19,650
You may go.

794
00:40:20,090 --> 00:40:20,970
Yes.

795
00:40:25,170 --> 00:40:27,890
Where is the female lead

796
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:30,650
who transmigrated into this book?

797
00:40:39,630 --> 00:40:40,830
I have to find a way

798
00:40:40,850 --> 00:40:42,400
to leave a noticeable mark.

799
00:40:43,250 --> 00:40:44,790
One that only my kind would notice.
